\alpha, y\in\mathbb{R}
\vert y\vert<1
y=-4x
\alpha=-1/2
 {-\frac{1}{2}\choose r}(-4x)^r= {2r\choose r}x^r
 (1+y)^\alpha=\sum_{r=0}^\infty {\alpha \choose r}y^r 
 \frac{1}{\sqrt{1-4x}}=\sum_{r=0}^\infty {-\frac{1}{2}\choose r}(-4x)^r 
{-\frac{1}{2}\choose r}(-4x)^r={2r \choose r}x^r
  {-\frac{1}{2}\choose r}(-4x)^r= \frac{(-1/2)\cdots (-1/2-(r-1))}{r!}(-4)^rx^r=\frac{2^r(2r-1)(2r-3)\cdots 1}{r!}x^r 
 2^r\frac{(2r-1)(2r-3)\cdots 1}{r!}\frac{r!}{r!}= \frac{(2r-1)\cdots 1}{r!}\frac{2r(2r-2)\cdots 2}{r!}=\frac{(2r)!}{r!r!}={2r \choose r} 
